  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs tunable configuration parameters including base mesh size (target y+ ≈ 1, nominal element edge length 0.12 mm in gap regions), a Lagrangian hemolysis integration time-step multiplier (set to 0.05 during validation), and a scalar damage accumulation threshold below which sub-threshold stress exposures are discarded (set to 2 Pa·s during validation runs). Validation results are reported 'at the chosen settings' and show RH < 1 across all five operating points. However, no structured configuration node is linked to the package and the Context of Use does not constrain which parameter values must be used at deployment; a practitioner reproducing the analysis could silently alter any of these three parameters and obtain materially different hemolysis predictions without triggering a re-validation flag.",
