      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with regression test suite; configuration files stored under source control.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R1 used under institutional license with documented version control. Solver regression tests pass for internal flow benchmarks. Configuration files (case files, UDF source) are archived in the project repository. Note: tunable hemolysis post-processing parameters (time-step multiplier, damage threshold) are documented only in the methods narrative and are not formally version-locked in the archived case files."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark problems for rotating machinery internal flow at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent verified against FDA nozzle and rotating disk benchmarks. Discretization schemes (second-order upwind momentum, SIMPLEC pressure-velocity coupling) are consistent with published best practices for blood pump CFD."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude at critical locations.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 1.8M, medium 4.1M, fine 9.6M cells). GCI for area-averaged wall shear stress in the impeller gap is 3.2%. The nominal mesh edge length of 0.12 mm in gap regions was selected based on this study and used for all five validation operating points. The mesh size parameter is referenced in the narrative but is not encoded as a pinned configuration value in any structured field of this package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) match CFD inlet/outlet conditions within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test loop operated with porcine blood analog (glycerol-saline, viscosity 3.5 cP at 37°C). Flow rates set by Coriolis meter (±1% accuracy). Rotational speed controlled by servo drive (±0.2% accuracy). CFD boundary conditions assigned from logged experimental values; agreement within 2% for all five operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH within 15% of experimentally measured RH for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH values range from 0.71 to 0.94 across operating points. Experimental RH values from modified index of hemolysis (MIH) protocol. Maximum relative error between CFD and experiment is 11.4% at operating point 5. All five points satisfy the ±15% acceptance band. Results reported at the chosen settings for mesh resolution, Lagrangian time-step multiplier, and damage accumulation threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "RH is the primary regulatory QoI for blood pump hemolysis submissions per FDA guidance. The Lagrangian power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger constants) maps shear stress history to scalar damage index, which is integrated to yield MIH and then normalized to predicate device to produce RH. This QoI is directly compared against the RH < 1 acceptance criterion specified in the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid, and operating range are representative of the CPB COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the subject device. Fluid properties, rotational speed range (2000–4000 RPM), and flow range (2–6 L/min) span the CPB operating envelope. Predicate device hemolysis data obtained from same experimental protocol. Validation activities are therefore directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
