      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model selection, hemolysis constitutive law) not formally assessed at MRL 2. SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for blood pump internal flows."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and boundary condition values traceable to measurement or published reference.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity measured with cone-plate rheometer (ISO 6721). Density from vendor datasheet. Pump geometry from CMM-verified CAD. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream piping calculations. All inputs documented in the simulation report. The hemolysis model coefficients (α = 3.62×10⁻⁵, β = 2.416, γ = 0.785) are taken from Giersiepen et al. and cited; however, the damage accumulation threshold parameter (2 Pa·s) used in the Lagrangian post-processor is described only in the methods text and is not listed as a structured model input in this package."
    },
